# Task #120: a FAILED fetch-on-launch must (a) show a readable red-screen cause, (b) leave
# the 0-byte cloud stub INTACT so the emulator fails fast on an empty file — never a deleted
# entry, never fake progress — and (c) still exit 0 (a pre-launch hook cannot cancel the launch).
desc fetch hook (#120): failed download leaves the 0-byte stub intact + honest error screen
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
sdfile Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
engine 4|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --download
expect_trace SHOW2 simple text='The server had a problem sending this game — try again. The game screen that follows will fail to open — that's expected. Fix the connection and launch again.'
expect_file_empty Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
